            "type": "html",
            "text": "\nSimilarly, the exokernel concept provides no equivalent to policy-setting. Exokernels exist solely to multiplex hardware safely. It is free to employ <i>any means necessary</i> to make good on its policy-free \"policy.\" This is why you'll often see such dirty tricks as dynamically downloaded chunks of code.",
            "id": "12ac22b2c39a6f46b6458770f68e8fd7"
