            "type": "html",
            "text": "\nXok uses this approach for managing competing filesystem access on a disk too. However, disk management is substantially more sophisticated than network management, it nonetheless is doable with stellar performance levels. The results of running a webserver under Xok indicated <i>over 8x I/O throughput</i> than a typical web server on monolithic kernel environment, including when accessing many small files. This strongly suggests the method is viable and produces superlative performance.",
            "id": "d2d1fad5205442e8d966be386e515939"
